ty\">Vacuum activity</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Workhouse\" title=\"Workhouse\">Workhouse</a></li></ul>\n</div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Busy_work&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/busywork\">\"Definition of BUSYWORK\"</a>. <i>www.merriam-webster.com</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2018-08-30</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=www.merriam-webster.com&amp;rft.atitle=Definition+of+BUSYWORK&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.merriam-webster.com%2Fdictionary%2Fbusywork&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABusy+work\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-BostonPTA-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-BostonPTA_2-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-BostonPTA_2-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-BostonPTA_2-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-BostonPTA_2-3\"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-BostonPTA_2-4\"><sup><i><b>e</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">(1901) <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=n2BMAAAAIAAJ&amp;printsec=frontcover#v=onepage&amp;q&amp;f=false\">Plans for busy work - Boston Primary Teachers' Association - Google Books</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite id=\"CITEREFPaul_Monroe1910\" class=\"citation\"><a href=\"/wiki/Paul_Monroe\" title=\"Paul Monroe\">Paul Monroe</a> (1910), \"Busy work\", <i>A Cyclopedia of Education</i>, p.&#160;475</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=Busy+work&amp;rft.btitle=A+Cyclopedia+of+Education&amp;rft.pages=475&amp;rft.date=1910&amp;rft.au=Paul+Monroe&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABusy+work\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Slack-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-Slack_4-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Slack_4-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Slack_4-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">(2001) <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=3AuP7HV14SYC&amp;printsec=frontcover#v=onepage&amp;q&amp;f=false\">Slack: Getting Past Burnout, Busywork, and the Myth of Total Efficiency - Tom DeMarco - Google Books </a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Kotter, John (January 19, 2012). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.forbes.com/sites/johnkotter/2012/01/19/why-busy-work-doesnt-work/\">\"Why Busy Work Doesn't Work\"</a>. Forbes Magazine<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">September 1,</span> 2012</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Why+Busy+Work+Doesn%27t+Work&amp;rft.pub